.\" termin.al-name: find
.\" termin.al-usage: find [path] [-name pattern]
.\" termin.al-summary: Find virtual paths by a simple wildcard name pattern.
.TH FIND 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
find \- Find virtual paths by a simple wildcard name pattern.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
find [path] [-name pattern]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Searches virtual entry names beneath a starting directory. The name expression supports the simple wildcard matching documented below.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -name pattern
Match entry names with * and ? wildcards. The option may follow or precede the path.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ find -name '*.md'
$ find projects -name '*project*'
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
help(1), man(1)
